<br>
How do you prove they are abusing/violationg calendar rules?  Can I submit a doctored screenshot as evidence?  How about a doctored log file?  Can I be a nefarious spy choose my timing of the /who correctly so as people log in or are ressed in from a CR such that I can demonstrate clearly the guild was missing one person shy of the 2/3 rule?  Now I have successfully demonstrated I have no life and removed one poster from the calendar for X time.<br>
<br>
I think you are going about it all wrong.  You are trying to set up the same atmosphere we just had of mistrust, where people take it upon themselves to spy on others and try to make others look bad.  If you make the requirements strict enough up front, you cut out more potential for abuse proactively.  If you make it so that to post you have to have 36 planesable toons, verify these up front.  You save yourself a lot of headache, since it's all publicly posted who is in alliance with whom (ahead of time) and spot checks by impartial people can verify quickly to make sure no blatant abuses are happening.  72 players piggybacking in Hate or Fear still only has X drops to deal with, but they are also pretty obvious (and pretty laggy).<br>
<br>
   Heck, if you make it so that guilds/alliances have to have 36 or 42 members just to post, the 2/3 rule really doesn't matter all that much, short of Guild/Alliance A bringing large numbers to Guild/Alliance B's raid, and vice versa.  I would hate to see someone lose their posting priviledges because someone else chose a bad CR time to do /who, and they wind up one person short, or worse, someone doctor log files.  The key to any good plan, is keep it simple.<br>
<br>
36 min planesable toons publicly posted under a section of the RTA just to post.<br>
<br>
If you stick with 2/3, try not to be sticklers for decimal points. . .someone has to log, under the strictest rules an invite is forced need to leave - a piece of armor he needs no one else can use drops.  You have missed the forest for the trees.  <br>
<br>
The punishments you list make sense. . .for someone who has made a blatant violation.<br>
<br>
</font><P>Karadin Firethorne
Blackguard of the Rathe
