Have 36 min toons to post and only up to 6 invites from a paticular guild should remove the abuses that the 2/3 rule was put in place for.<br>
<br>
And no I don't advocate Calendar Nazi's that are always checking up on people.  But the calender itself is easy to check and generally is pretty much by the rules.  Being able to delete posts (supposed to be part of the new calendar I believe) should remove all confusion as to who has which plane on a day and make abuserers stand out more.<br>
<br>
Not calling in the &quot;Epic&quot; guild of the day is an easy one to figure out.  If the god is up the next day, the violated that rule.<br>
<br>
As for on site planes inspections.  Well I'm a monk, and you know that we can't go anywhere without at least one cleric, so it won't be me doing the checking.  But others already do pop up there and check, and if you can blantently breaking the rules, then you should be nervious.<br>
<br>
However, I agree that we need to get the 36 toons posted before someone can post.  And have the consequence/punishments such that people will not break the rules.</font><P>Milambus Mandragon<BR>
